  "texts": [
    "Once again, we conclude that the 20 fJ per random bit, reported in ref.",
    "28 underestimates the costs of RNG generation by about an order of magnitude when the RNG quality and other peripheries such as LUTs are carefully taken into account.",
    "In this paper, we do not reproduce the energy estimation of the sMTJ-based p-bit but report the estimate in ref.",
    "28, which assumes an sMTJ-based p-bit with ≈ nanosecond fluctuations.",
    "Our benchmarking results highlight the true expense of highquality digital p-bits in silicon implementations."
  ],
